p://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Is Better Than You</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#939393>(4/7/02 11:49:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=109.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Shadow Knight, Help please</span><hr size=1> Reroll and put 5 points into agility and 5 points into intelligence then 10 into stamina.  You're an Ogre, you're slow and dumb, fix that!  You have enough stamina, but there's never 'too much' (pre-255 =P). <p><img src=http://www.raarcentral.com/zizar/scarlita.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udaelem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daelem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#939393>(4/8/02 6:09:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=109.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Shadow Knight, Help please</span><hr size=1> Without the 5 points into Agility your AC will suffer bigtime.<br><br>As far as rightclick items for a 'low lvl' SK that are usefull, there is only one and thats Pre-Nerf CoS for rightclick instant invis OR Post nerf for 5 sec cast time.  Post nerf is not that great but it is useable at lvl 20 which is 8 lvls sooner than you will be able to cast it yourself and it keeps that spell slot open.<br><br>Bloodember isn't useable till lvl 45, but BE guantlets(engulfing darkness) are a usefull tool at times, and if you take the time to experiment BE boot(Fear) can make soloing easier for any race of SK. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=tit